gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 140, Suns 129
gameRecap.excerpt: Milwaukee knocks down a season-high 24 3PT FGs to defeat Phoenix, 140-129. For Milwaukee, Damian Lillard led the way with 31 points, 5 rebounds, and a career-high tying 16 assists while aided by Bobby Portis (31 points, 10 rebounds, three steals) in the victory. Bradley Beal finished with 28 points and seven assists with Grayson Allen recording 25 points (six 3PM) and eight assists and Devin Booker adding 23 points, nine rebounds, and six assists for Phoenix in the losing effort. Milwaukee improves to 44-24, while Phoenix moves to 39-29 in the loss.
